    <forecast>
        <area aac="SA_FA001" description="South Australia" type="region">
            <forecast-period start-time-local="2026-04-07T04:10:44+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-07T04:10:44+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-06T18:40:44Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-06T18:40:44Z">
                <text type="warning_summary_footer">For latest warnings go to www.bom.gov.au, subscribe to RSS feeds, call 1300 659 210* or listen for warnings on relevant TV and radio broadcasts.</text>
                <text type="synoptic_situation">A cold front will pass over the southeast this morning followed by a high-pressure system building south of the state today. The high will then move east on Wednesday allowing an upper trough to bring instability to southern parts of the state during the day, persisting into Thursday. The upper trough will precede a vigorous cold front that is forecast to move over South Australia Thursday afternoon. A cooler southwest to southerly flow will gradually moderate as a stronger high-pressure system moves in from the west from Friday to be south of the state on Sunday.</text>
                <text type="product_footer">* Calls to 1300 numbers cost around 27.5c incl. GST, higher from mobiles or public phones.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
        <area aac="SA_PW010" description="West Coast" type="public-district" parent-aac="SA_FA001">
            <forecast-period index="0" start-time-local="2026-04-07T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-08T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-06T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-07T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Cloudy. Very high chance of showers, most likely during the morning and afternoon. The chance of a thunderstorm west of Nullarbor. Winds southeasterly 15 to 20 km/h turning easterly 15 to 25 km/h during the day. Daytime maximum temperatures in the low 20s.</text>
                <text type="fire_danger">No Rating</text>
                <text type="uv_alert">Sun protection 9:40am to 3:30pm, UV Index predicted to reach 7 [High]</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="1" start-time-local="2026-04-08T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-09T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-07T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-08T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. Medium chance of showers, most likely in the morning. The chance of a thunderstorm. Winds north to northeasterly 15 to 25 km/h tending north to northwesterly in the middle of the day then tending southeast to southwesterly 15 to 20 km/h in the late afternoon. Overnight temperatures falling to between 13 and 16 with daytime temperatures reaching around 30.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="2" start-time-local="2026-04-09T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-10T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-08T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-09T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. High chance of showers east of Ceduna, medium chance elsewhere. The chance of a thunderstorm in the morning and afternoon. Light winds becoming south to southwesterly 20 to 30 km/h during the morning then tending west to southwesterly 15 to 25 km/h during the evening. Overnight temperatures falling to around 16 with daytime temperatures reaching the low to mid 20s.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="3" start-time-local="2026-04-10T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-11T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-09T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-10T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Cloudy. Slight chance of a shower. Winds southwesterly 20 to 30 km/h. Overnight temperatures falling to around 14 with daytime temperatures reaching the low 20s.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
